<sect1 id="FromGregorianDate">
  <title><emphasis role="bold">FromGregorianDate</emphasis></title>

  <para><emphasis role="bold">STD.Date.FromGregorianDate<indexterm>
      <primary>STD.Date.FromGregorianDate</primary>
    </indexterm><indexterm>
      <primary>Date.FromGregorianDate</primary>
    </indexterm>(</emphasis> <emphasis>date</emphasis> <emphasis
  role="bold">)</emphasis></para>

  <informaltable colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
    <tgroup cols="2">
      <colspec colwidth="80.50pt" />

      <colspec />

      <tbody>
        <row>
          <entry><emphasis>date</emphasis></entry>

          <entry>Um Date_t value.</entry>
        </row>

        <row>
          <entry>Return:</entry>

          <entry>FromGregorianDate retorna um valor UNSIGNED4.</entry>
        </row>
      </tbody>
    </tgroup>
  </informaltable>

  <para>A função  <emphasis role="bold">FromGregorianDate</emphasis>  retorna um valor Date_t do parâmetro  <emphasis>date</emphasis>  que representa o número de dias desde 31 de dezembro de 1 BC no calendário gregoriano (consulte as FAQ do calendário, por Claus Tondering, em http://www.tondering.dk/claus/calendar.html).</para>

  <para>Exemplo:</para>

  <programlisting format="linespecific">IMPORT STD; UNSIGNED4 MyDate := 20120101; D := STD.Date.FromGregorianDate(MyDate); //D contains 734503
  </programlisting>

  <para></para>
</sect1>
